- Login to your esxi host web panel navigate to storage and click on new datastore
- Select Create new VMFS datastore.
- Give a Name to datastore and Click on next.
- Select use full disk and Click on next.
- We get an error then click on yes.
- Expand The Storage of esxi to 800 GB.
- Select the olive green division at left to set the storage for VMFS by moving the above bar.  
- Click on Finish
- Too expand the storage select expand and click on next.
- Select the newly created datastore.
- Set the storage by scrolling bar allocate both the vmfs and free space  a similar storage. 
- Our VMFS expanded Click on Finish.
- Login vcenter and go to storage and new data store.
- Select VMFS and Click on next.
- Our datastore is created 

- Navigate to vcenter ->storage.
- Go to Delete datastore and click yes

